memberdef.name: Process

briefdescription.para: Main method that processes functors.

detaileddescription.para: For each object, it will call the functor. Depending on the code returned by the functor, it will also process it for all children. The Filters class parameter makes is possible to process only objects of a type that matches the attribute value given in the Comparison object. This is the generic way for parsing the tree, e.g., for extracting one single staff or layer. Deepness specifies how many child levels should be processed. UNLIMITED_DEPTH means no limit (EditorialElement objects do not count). skipFirst does not call the functor or endFunctor on the first (calling) level
